classlib: Function:-asBuffer, -plot: use sampleRate to infer control rate data, clean/update docs (#6217)

This fixes https://github.com/supercollider/supercollider/issues/6206.

* classlib: Function:-asBuffer: set sampleRate based on function's output rate

-asBuffer:
- consolidate waiting and syncing
- rename vars so context is clearer
-plot:
- read buffer sample rate for frame duration

* classlib: Buffer:-query: disambiguate vars msg and addr, correct and update docs

---------

class library: MultiOutUGen: better error for non-numeric numChannels arg (#6190)

MultiOutUGens now throw a more readable error for non-integer numChannels argument. Since OutputProxy will fail on a non-integer `argIndex` argument already, this does not limit existing uses.

commit.message:
Add atomic bool const to lockLanguageOrQuit in PyrSched.h (#6229)

Change lockLanguageOrQuit to use std::atomic<bool> const&

Modified the lockLanguageOrQuit function in PyrSched.h to take a constant reference to std::atomic.

The actual problem was that the function took the atomic flag by value instead of by reference. This made the repeated checks entirely redundant and as a consequence it would not notice when the flag has changed in between, undermining the very purpose of this function.

Co-authored-by: Bernardo Barros <bernardo.barros@protonmail.ch>

Add atomic bool const to lockLanguageOrQuit in PyrSched.h (#6229)

Change lockLanguageOrQuit to use std::atomic<bool> const&

Modified the lockLanguageOrQuit function in PyrSched.h to take a constant reference to std::atomic.

The actual problem was that the function took the atomic flag by value instead of by reference. This made the repeated checks entirely redundant and as a consequence it would not notice when the flag has changed in between, undermining the very purpose of this function.
